This app is my favorite lab app out there.  Thank you for such a great product.  This has been a wonderful companion in Nursing School.  The other day I needed levels for Myoglobin and could not find it.  It is an important cardiac marker.  Please add it to the app.  Thank you again for a great app.
Great

Love this with all my heart. Its a nursing lab bible in my pocket. Saves so much time and effort and has the indications for abnormal high/low values that could help you relate to your pts dx. Worth every penny!!
Very very good lab reference
Good
Easily look up lab values. Not much more to say.

Awesome app. Love it! All values i need as a medical student are found here
Everything you need is right there. Can sort by category or panels. Also if you don't understand what a particular lab value is indicative, there's a page explaining it too.
Good
Nice interface. Very useful Ready reconner

For lab values this is the app to have on hand. I have 3 other apps on my ipad but only 1 for my note 3 and this is it. I love how you can add your own notes as it makes this app stand out from the others and not to mention the ease of it and so many lab markers. Keep up the great work.
Easy to use and well laid out.  can easily search labs using full name or abbreviations.

I'm constantly having to look up reference ranges for biochemistry results so having this app by my side is really handy. It also allows me to modify ranges and units to those I need and make notes to aid study. The only addition I'd like would be the ability to create custom measurements and groupings e.g., infection markers.
Overall great App. Let's see if future updates will provide more rare parameters (eg onco etc.). If so then I would say 5 stars.

Good lay out. Clear explanation of the tests. I'm impressed. Guess it's time to remove all other similar apps. I like the part where you can add your own notes. The only limitation is you can't automatically transfer the notes to other devices.
This app is really beneficial. I use it all the time.
This app helped so much when I was studying in Nursing school & for NCLEX-RN	Yep
The BEST One!
As a pharmacist, I am happy to have an application that helps with difficult-to-remember lab values. One of the must-have medical apps.
...what I need!
I can customize the values,  make fav lists,  add notes,  it's easy to read,  has color icons,  this app is the best I have seen yet.  I am flight crew member and used this for FP-C exam.
Useful. Does what it says.. Looks nice too. It would be great to be able to save edits/notes I've made and transfer them to a different device.
Excellent app!!!
It's great this has a few indications with the various labs - very handy for reviewing those labs not used frequently or when your brain needs a little reminder
Love this app it has helped me a great deal in Nursing school.
App is designed really well and has some potential. Unfortunately there is wrong/missing info, especially in the differential diagnosis section...
Bad app. Will not download to zte

This app has been a lifesaver for my acute rotation.  Well worth the $3!!  Thank you!
Highly recommended for health professionals.
Great app for a quick look. Highly recommend it.
Best lab app out there.
So glad it's made it here! Loved this app on iTunes! Used a lot in both studying& clinical practice. The developer is very responsive.
Finally a great lab values app on Android. It has lots of values, good descriptions, and I love the differentials. Easy recommendation!
App is super easy to use and quite comprehensive.  Developer is lightning fast with responses.  I had a question, emailed dev., and got a reply in minutes.
